<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Embassy in Italy</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v03</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d575</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">575</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-04-09T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="575" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.48/4–947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Italy</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-09T18:00:00-05:00">April 9, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>504. Preliminary conversation held with representatives Italian Govt. March 27 re
                    U.S. relief assistance.</p>
                <p>Memo of conversation will be forwarded.</p>
                <p>Have delivered tentative draft agreement Italian reps, containing terms operation
                    U.S. and Italy and including restrictions and requirements bill in
                        Congress.<note n="1" xml:id="d575fn1">The draft text of the proposed
                        agreement was sent to Rome in the Department’s telegraphic instruction 895,
                        June 11, not printed (805.48/6–1147).</note> Ital. reps. probably will
                    forward Rome draft. Copies draft agreements dispatched today ur info. Send
                    comments immediately.</p>
                <p>No agreements will be signed until final passage Congress end April. Ital reps,
                    asked submit tentative relief import food needs May June, July.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
